-- Staging table for subscriptions with enriched dimension data
WITH source AS (
    SELECT
        s.subscription_id,
        s.user_id,
        s.plan_id,
        s.started_at,
        s.ended_at,
        s.status,

)

    subscription_id,
    user_id,
    plan_id,
    started_at,
    ended_at,
    status,
    tier
FROM source

```sql
-- Staging table for users with company information
WITH source AS (
    SELECT
        u.user_id,
        u.name,
        u.email,
        u.company_id,
        COALESCE(c.industry, '(unknown)') AS industry
    FROM users u
    LEFT JOIN companies c
        ON c.company_id = u.company_id
)
SELECT
    user_id,
    name,
    email,
    company_id,
    industry
FROM source
```

-- stg_billing_events.sql
```sql
-- Staging table for billing events with deduplication
WITH source AS (
    SELECT
        event_id,
        subscription_id,
        event_month,
        amount,
        event_type,
        ROW_NUMBER() OVER (
            PARTITION BY subscription_id, event_month
            ORDER BY event_id DESC
        ) AS row_num
    FROM billing_events
)
SELECT
    subscription_id,
    event_month,
    amount,
    event_type
FROM source
WHERE row_num = 1
```

WITH source AS (
    SELECT
        s.subscription_id,
        s.user_id,
        s.tier,
        DATE_TRUNC('month', b.event_month)::DATE AS event_month
    FROM {{ ref('stg_subscriptions') }} s
    LEFT JOIN {{ ref('stg_billing_events') }} b
        ON b.subscription_id = s.subscription_id
    WHERE b.event_month IS NOT NULL
)
SELECT
    subscription_id,
    user_id,
    tier,
    event_month
FROM source

-- Monthly subscription metrics aggregated by month, tier, and industry
WITH subscription_months AS (
    SELECT
        im.event_month,
        im.tier,
        u.industry,
        im.subscription_id,
        im.user_id,
        b.amount
    FROM {{ ref('int_subscription_months') }} im
    LEFT JOIN {{ ref('stg_users') }} u
        ON u.user_id = im.user_id
    LEFT JOIN {{ ref('stg_billing_events') }} b
        ON b.subscription_id = im.subscription_id
        AND DATE_TRUNC('month', b.event_month)::DATE = im.event_month
)
SELECT
    event_month AS month,
    tier,
    industry,
    COUNT(DISTINCT subscription_id) AS active_subscriptions,
    SUM(amount) AS total_mrr,
    COUNT(DISTINCT user_id) AS unique_users
FROM subscription_months
GROUP BY
    event_month,
    tier,
    industry
ORDER BY
    event_month,
    tier,
    industry
